n is selected from the group consisting of 1 to 20, inclusive.

In another embodiment, a dicationic liquid salt is provided. The dicationic liquid salt corresponds in structure to Formula (IV):



        A+-B-A'+     Formula (IV)



and at least one counter anion,

wherein:

A and A' are each a monoionic group independently selected from the group consisting of ammonium, thionium, phosphonium, arsonium, carbocylyl and heterocyclyl;

wherein each such substituent is optionally substituted with one or more substituents selected from the group consisting of alkyl, hydroxyl, alkoxy, cycloalkyl, aryl, hydroxyalkyl, cycloalkylalkyl and aralkyl;

wherein A and A' are different or A and A' have at least one different substituent;
B is a divalent fragment composed of one or more moieties selected from the group consisting of alkylene, alkenylene, alkynylene, (-CH2-carbocyclyl-CH2-)n, and polysiloxyl;

wherein alkylene, alkenylene, and alkynylene optionally contain one or more heteroatoms selected from the group consisting of O, N, S or Si;

wherein B is optionally substituted with one or more substituents selected from the group consisting of alkyl, alkenyl, alkynyl, and alkoxy;
n is selected from the group consisting of 1 to 20, inclusive.

In another embodiment, a method is provided for separating one chemical from a mixture of chemicals. The method comprises the steps of:
providing a mixture of at least one first and at least one second chemical;
exposing the mixture to a solid support containing one or more dicationic liquid salts according to Formula (III) and/or Formula (IV), wherein the one or more dicationic liquid salts is adsorbed, absorbed or immobilized on the support, and retaining at least a portion of the first chemical on the solid support.

